
Overview of noun pyjama

The noun pyjama has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                       
1. pajama, pyjama -- (a pair of loose trousers tied by a drawstring around the waist; worn by men and women in some Asian countries)
2. pajama, pyjama, pj's, jammies -- ((usually plural) loose-fitting nightclothes worn for sleeping or lounging; have a jacket top and trousers)
